TITLE: Vertical and Horizontal Layout
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create vertical and horizontal layouts using the vertical! and horizontal! macros with area calculations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ratatui/ratatui/blob/main/ratatui-macros/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use ratatui_macros::{vertical, horizontal};

let area = Rect { x: 0, y: 0, width: 10, height: 10 };

let [main, bottom] = vertical![==100%, >=3].areas(area);

assert_eq!(bottom.y, 7);
assert_eq!(bottom.height, 3);

let [left, main, right] = horizontal![>=3, ==100%, >=3].areas(area);

assert_eq!(left.width, 3);
assert_eq!(right.width, 3);
```

