TITLE: Adding WidgetRef and StatefulWidgetRef Traits in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This snippet introduces new traits WidgetRef and StatefulWidgetRef, which allow rendering widgets by reference. It enables rendering boxed widgets and provides more flexibility in widget composition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ratatui/ratatui/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-23_snippet_57

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
struct Parent {
    child: Option<Child>,
}

impl WidgetRef for Parent {
    fn render_ref(&self, area: Rect, buf: &mut Buffer) {
        self.child.render_ref(area, buf);
    }
}
```

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
let widgets: Vec<Box<dyn WidgetRef>> = vec![Box::new(Greeting), Box::new(Farewell)];
for widget in widgets {
    widget.render_ref(buf.area, &mut buf);
}
assert_eq!(buf, Buffer::with_lines(["Hello        Goodbye"]));
```

